# bdusage project rules

## Product invariants

- Never mix **actual** (CUR / Cost Explorer billing) and **estimate** (CloudWatch Logs / Metrics) amounts in the same report row or total.
- Every cost report must print a `source:` line (e.g. `source: CUR 2.0 actual`).
- Actual costs use AWS billing data only; do not recompute actual totals from model list prices.
- Do not fetch, store, or display Bedrock invocation log bodies.

## Version scope

- Default implementation target: **v0.1** (ROADMAP Step 1–5): CUR DuckDB/Athena, CE fallback, Logs estimate, weekly, users — see `src/commands.ts`.
- Do not add **v0.2+** features (managed mode) unless the task explicitly requests a later version.
- Check [docs/ROADMAP.md](mdc:docs/ROADMAP.md) and [docs/SPEC.md](mdc:docs/SPEC.md) before changing CLI options or output format.

## Completion checklist

Before finishing a code change, run `bun run ci` and fix all failures.

## Code style

- TypeScript ESM; use `.js` extensions in import specifiers.
- Match existing tooling: oxlint, Biome, Vitest, knip — do not introduce ESLint/Prettier unless requested.
- Keep diffs minimal; avoid unrelated refactors.

## Communication

- User-facing README: Japanese.
- SPEC / ROADMAP / ADRs: Japanese unless the file is already English.
- Do not end responses with open-ended "let me know if you want…" offers.
